<h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Patch 36 (September 30, 2014)</h4><ul><li><b>Impale (E)</b></li><ul><li> Fixed a bug where this ability would sometimes flip an enemy after they exited this ability's cast range.</li></ul><li><b>Shore's Calling (R)</b></li><ul><li> Fixed a bug where this ability would sometimes heal Cerulean for less than the intended amount against targets between 70% to 100% Health.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 34 (August 19th, 2014)</h4><ul><li><b>Ritual Bulwark (W)</b></li><ul><li>The flat Armor and Magic Resistance bonus granted when activating this ability has been reduced to 20/30/40/50/60, down from 25/35/45/55/65.</li><li>The decaying Armor and Magic Resistance bonus granted when activating this ability has been reduced to 20/30/40/50/60, down from 25/35/45/55/65.</li></ul><li><b>Shore's Calling (R)</b></li><ul><li>The cooldown of this ability has been increased to 110/100/90, up from 100/85/70.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 31 (June 17th, 2014)</h4><ul><li><B>Whirling Strike (Q)</B></li><ul><li>Fixed a bug that would occasionally allow multiple casts of this ability if activated several times within a short period of time.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 29 (May 5th, 2014)</h4><ul><li><b>Impale (E)</b></li><ul><li>The base damage of this ability has been reduced to 70/115/160/205/250, down from 80/125/170/215/260.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 26 (Feb 24, 2014)</h4><ul><li>Whirling Strike (Q)<ul><li>The displayed range of this ability has been updated to 380, from previous value of 425.</li></ul><li>Impale (E)</li><ul><li>The range of this ability has been reduced by 10%.</li></ul><li>Shore's Calling (R)</li><ul><li>The displayed range of this ability has been updated to 585, from previous value of 650.</li><li>The Power ratio of this ability has been reduced to 0.8, down from 0.9.</li></ul></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 16 (Oct 31, 2013)</h4><ul><li>Shore's Calling (R) will now go on cooldown even if the target of the ability dies when Cerulean is in mid animation. Cerulean will also now heal the correct amount if the target dies mid animation.</li></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 7 (August 02, 2013)</h4><ul><li>Basic attack range increased to 130, up from 95.</li></ul>